CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 4, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "Theresa Ann Jeter And Mother...First prize winner in Carnation Baby Contest" "Winner And Mother - Four-month-old Theresa Ann Jeter, of Finleyville, shown with her mother, Mrs. Charlene Jeter, won the $300 first prize check as healthiest champion baby of the Pittsburgh District in Carnation Milk Company's Healthy Baby Contest.  Baby Theresa is 18 1/2 pounds and is 26 1/2 inches in height."
TitMainTitle: John Ruffing Jr. presenting first prize to Theresa Ann Jeter, daughter of Charlene Jeter, in Centre Avenue YMCA during Carnation Milk baby contest
